KKBox Music Streaming — Churn Prediction

Predicting subscriber churn using machine learning on 21.5 million transaction records
MSc IT for Business Data Analytics — Capstone Project


Overview
This project builds and evaluates a machine learning pipeline to predict whether a KKBox music streaming subscriber will churn — defined as failing to renew their membership within 30 days of expiry.
Five models are trained in order of complexity and compared across three metrics:
ModelROC-AUCLog LossPR-AUCDummy Classifier0.49814.29900.0637Logistic Regression0.80360.50260.3401Random Forest0.87510.41310.4595XGBoost0.87910.40210.4824LightGBM (Optuna)0.87680.21510.4571
LightGBM is the recommended production model — it achieves near-identical ranking performance to XGBoost but with 47% better probability calibration (Log Loss), which matters when churn scores are used to allocate retention budgets across risk tiers.

