How to Run
Step 1 — Open in Google Colab
Upload kkbox_churn.py to Colab or copy the code into a notebook.
Step 2 — Mount Google Drive
pythonfrom google.colab import drive
drive.mount('/content/drive')
Step 3 — Set up Kaggle credentials
Upload your kaggle.json file (from kaggle.com → Settings → API):
pythonfrom google.colab import files
files.upload()   # select kaggle.json
Step 4 — Run the script
The script will:

Download the competition files from Kaggle automatically
Apply the leakage fix (transaction cutoff)
Engineer all features
Save a features.parquet file to Drive (skips steps 1–3 on future runs)
Train all 5 models
Generate all evaluation plots and save them to Drive

Step 5 — Subsequent sessions
On your next session the script detects features.parquet on Drive and loads it in ~5 seconds, skipping the entire data preparation pipeline.

