Results
SHAP Feature Importance
Top 3 drivers of churn (by mean absolute SHAP value):

auto_renew_rate — highest importance by far; disabling auto-renewal is the strongest churn signal
recency_days — users inactive before the cutoff are at elevated risk
cancel_rate — history of manual cancellations predicts future churn

Demographic features (age, city, gender) contribute but are substantially less important than behavioural features.
Business Recommendations
PriorityActionTarget Segment1Auto-renewal re-enrolment campaignUsers with auto_renew_rate < 0.52Proactive retention outreachUsers with cancel_rate > 0.4 in last 90 days3Structured onboarding programmeNew subscribers with tenure_days < 90

Reproducibility

Random seed 42 used throughout all splits, models, and Optuna trials
All train/val/test splits are stratified to preserve the 6.4% churn rate
Medians for imputation are computed from the training set only
The features.parquet file on Drive guarantees identical feature inputs across sessions


